STATE of North Carolina
v.
Kevin Salvador GOLPHIN No. 114P17 Supreme Court of North Carolina. November 8, 2017 Mr. Kevin Salvado Golphin, for Golphin, Kevin Salvador. Mr. Daniel P. O'Brien, Special Deputy Attorney General, Mr. William R. West, District Attorney, For State of N.C. Mr. Thomas Maher, Attorney at Law, Chapel Hill. Mr. Glenn G. Gerding, Appellate Defender.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 10th of April 2017 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Cumberland County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed without prejudice to Defendant's right to seek appropriate relief in the trial court. By order of the Court in conference, this the 8th of November 2017."
